{{Nihongo|'''Danrin-ji'''|檀林寺}} was [[Japan]]'s first [[Zen]] temple, founded in [[Saga (Kyoto district)|Saga]], [[Kyōto]] by order of [[Tachibana no Kachiko]] during the [[Jōwa (Heian period)|Jōwa era]]. The temple was destroyed by fire in 928, but was restored, and during the [[Muromachi period]] the temple was designated as one of Kyōto's five great Buddhist nunneries. The temple eventually fell into disrepair, and in 1339 construction of [[Tenryū-ji]] began on its grounds.
