{{Infobox scientist |name = Yuri Sergeevich Savenko |native_name = Юрий Сергеевич Савенко |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = |birth_place = [[Soviet Union]] |death_date = |death_place = |residence = [[Moscow]] |citizenship = {{Plainlist| * {{flag|the Soviet Union}} (1946–1991) * {{flag|Russia}} (1991–up to the present) }} |nationality = [[Ukraine|Russian]] |ethnicity = |fields = [[Psychiatry]] |workplaces = the [[Independent Psychiatric Association of Russia]] |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor = |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = |notable_students = |known_for = [[Human rights]] activism |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |awards = the award of the [[Moscow Helsinki Group]] "for historic contribution to the defence of human rights and the human rights movement" |religion = |signature = <!--(filename only)--> |footnotes = }}
'''Yuri Sergeevich Savenko''' ({{lang-ru|Ю́рий Серге́евич Саве́нко}}) is a Russian psychiatrist, the president since 1989 of the [[Independent Psychiatric Association of Russia]].<ref name="Savenko, Perekhov">{{cite journal|author1=Savenko, Yuri |author2=Perekhov, Alexei |title=The State of Psychiatry in Russia|journal=[[Psychiatric Times]]|date=13 February 2014|url=http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/special-reports/state-psychiatry-russia}}</ref><ref name="20-летие">{{cite journal |author=Савенко, Юрий|title=20-летие НПА России |journal=[[Nezavisimiy Psikhiatricheskiy Zhurnal]] |volume= |issue=№ 1 |pages=5–18 |year=2009 |issn=1028-8554 |url=http://www.npar.ru/pdf/2009-1.pdf}}</ref> He is also a member of the Council of Experts of the Russian Commissioner for Human Rights in the [[Russian Federation]].<ref name="Savenko, Perekhov"/><ref name="Гурьянова">{{cite news|author=Гурьянова, Татьяна|title=Юрий Cавенко: "Психически больные нуждаются в поддержке"|url=http://www.aif.ru/health/article/22058|accessdate=25 July 2011|newspaper=«АиФ Здоровье» №43|date=23 October 2008}}</ref> He holds M.D. qualification<ref name="Mercer">{{cite book|author1=Mercer, Ellen |author2=Mesner, Lea |title=An International psychiatric directory|year=1993|publisher=American Psychiatric Pub|isbn=0-89042-248-6|pages=184|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HFXiRMYA3QkC&&pg=PA184}}</ref>{{rp|184}} and is [[editor-in-chief]] of and a regular contributor to the ''[[Nezavisimiy Psikhiatricheskiy Zhurnal]]'', which has been published since 1991.<ref name="Savenko, Perekhov"/><ref name="Журнал">{{cite web |url=http://www.npar.ru/journal/ |title=About ''Nezavisimiy Psikhiatricheskiy Zhurnal'' |publisher=НПА |accessdate=2010-03-21}}</ref> He had been working as editorial consultant of the ''[[Moskovskiy Psikhoterapevticheskiy Zhurnal]]'' (“Moscow Journal for Psychotherapy”) for many years before he left this position in 2008.<ref>See the title pages of the following issues: * Московский психотерапевтический журнал, 1994, № 2. * Московский психотерапевтический журнал, 2007, № 3.</ref>
Before defending his doctoral thesis, Savenko was expelled from the Institute of Psychiatry in 1974.<ref name="Никакие">{{cite journal|author=Савенко, Юрий|title=Никакие жизненные коллизии не меняют нас с раннего детства…|journal=[[Nezavisimiy Psikhiatricheskiy Zhurnal]]|year=2009|issue=1|url=http://www.npar.ru/journal/2009/1/16-savenko.htm|accessdate=28 December 2010}}</ref>
His main works concern anxious psychotic syndromes,<ref name="Докт. дисс.">{{cite book|author=Савенко, Юрий|title=Тревожные психотические синдромы. Автореферат докт. дисс|year=1974|publisher=|location=Москва}}</ref> psychotic disorders problems, subject of psychiatry, and the [[classification of mental disorders]].<ref name="Навстречу МКБ-11">{{cite journal|author=Савенко, Юрий|title=Навстречу МКБ-11|trans-title=Toward the ICD-11|journal=[[Nezavisimiy Psikhiatricheskiy Zhurnal]]|year=2008|issue=3|url=http://www.npar.ru/journal/2008/3/02_mkb.htm|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref>
Yuri Savenko took part in a 'wrongful confinement' lawsuit filed in the [[European Court of Human Rights]] in 2003.<ref name="Brintlinger">{{cite book|author1=Brintlinger, Angela |author2=Vinitsky, Ilya |title=Madness and the mad in Russian culture|year=2007|publisher=University of Toronto Press|isbn=0-8020-9140-7|pages=294|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ED3U_XVLwHwC&pg=PA294}}</ref>{{rp|294}} When writing about this case, Savenko charged the [[Serbsky Institute]] with having a "pernicious effect on Russian medicine" and warned that the leadership of the psychiatric community "is now completely under the shadow of the state."<ref name="Brintlinger"/>{{rp|294}}
On 28 May 2009, Yuri Savenko wrote to the [[President of the Russian Federation]] [[Dmitry Medvedev]] an [[open letter]], in which Savenko asked Medvedev to submit to the [[State Duma]] a draft law prepared by the Independent Psychiatric Association of Russia to address a sharp drop in the level of forensic psychiatric examinations, which Savenko attributed to a lack of competition within the sector and its increasing nationalization.<ref name="Открытое письмо">{{cite journal|author=Савенко, Юрий|script-title=ru:Открытое письмо Президенту Российской Федерации Д.А. Медведеву|journal=[[Nezavisimiy Psikhiatricheskiy Zhurnal]]|year=2009|issue=№ 2|pages=5–6|url=http://www.npar.ru/journal/2009/2/medved.htm|accessdate=12 July 2011|language=ru}}</ref>
In 2009, Yuri Savenko and Valery Krasnov provided the leadership for the Second East European Congress of Psychiatry in Moscow.<ref name=Christodoulou>{{cite journal|title=The First Psychiatric Congress of Eastern Europe|journal=[[World Psychiatry (journal)|World Psychiatry]]|date=June 2008|volume=7|issue=2|page=128|doi=10.1002/j.2051-5545.2008.tb00177.x|pmid=18560477|author=Christodoulou, George|pmc=2408391}}</ref>
== Eugenic views == Savenko is a supporter of preventive [[eugenics]], he justifies [[enforced sterilization]] of women, which is practiced in Moscow psychoneurological nursing homes, and states that {{cquote|one needs a more strictly adjusted and open control over the practice of preventive eugenics, which, in itself, is, in its turn, justifiable.<ref name="Лишённые">{{cite news|title=Лишённые наследства. Законно ли запрещают рожать пациенткам психоневрологических интернатов?|url=http://2005.novayagazeta.ru/nomer/2005/93n/n93n-s26.shtml|accessdate=23 April 2012|newspaper=[[Novaya Gazeta]]|date=12 December 2005}} Савенко: «…Необходим более строго выверенный и открытый контроль за практикой предупредительной евгеники, которая сама по себе, в свою очередь, оправданна».</ref> }} However, Article 7 of Part 1 of the [[Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court]] defines enforced sterilization among [[crimes against humanity]].<ref name="Rome Statute">{{cite web|title=Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court|url=http://legal.un.org/icc/statute/romefra.htm|publisher=[[The International Criminal Court]]|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> In 2013, he seemed to take the opposite point of view and criticize German eugenics in the documentary ''Archetype. Neurosis. Libido. T-4 Death Squad'' produced by the [[Rossiya K]] TV channel.<ref>He says, “All statistics show Germany has the same rate of serious mental illness as that throughout the whole world. They reached nothing and only disgraced themselves.” Watch from 23:09 {{cite web|title=Archetype. Neurosis. Libido. T-4 Death Squad (TV documentary)|url=http://tvkultura.ru/video/show/brand_id/23166/video_id/640534|work=The [[Rossiya K]] TV channel|accessdate=18 October 2013}}</ref>
== Attitude to homosexuality == In 2005, Savenko as the president of the IPA expressed their joint surprise at the proposal by the [[Executive committee|Executive Committee]] of the [[American Psychiatric Association]] to exclude [[homosexuality]] as a mental disorder from manuals on psychiatry, referred the proposal to [[antipsychiatry|antipsychiatric actions]], and stated that ideological, social and liberal reasoning for the proposal was substituted for scientific one. His statement was put in the following words: “It is surprising for us that the substitution of ideological, social and liberal reasoning for scientific one came not from Russia and that the Executive Committee of the APA unanimously proposed to exclude homosexuality as a mental disorder from manuals on psychiatry. It shows that even the well-developed [[legal framework]] for psychiatry and the [[denationalization]] of [[Community mental health service|mental health service]] (by 80% in the USA), ie, the absence of two of the three factors that played a crucial role in Soviet abuses of psychiatry, does not protect against inherently antipsychiatric actions.”<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Савенко, Юрий |author2=Виноградова, Любовь |script-title=ru:Латентные формы антипсихиатрии как главная опасность|journal=[[Nezavisimiy Psikhiatricheskiy Zhurnal]]|year=2005|volume=№ 4|url=http://www.npar.ru/journal/2005/4/latent.htm|accessdate=4 May 2012|language=ru}}</ref> In 2014, Savenko changed his mind about homosexuality, and he and Perekhov in their joint paper criticized and referred the trend to consider homosexuality as a mental disorder to Soviet mentality that has endured into the present day.<ref name="Savenko, Perekhov"/>
== The resolution on Savenko == On 19 December 2013, the Commission on Professional Ethics Issues at the Board of the Russian Society of Psychiatrists delivered to Savenko when he raised ethical issues concerning the case of [[Mikhail Kosenko]] in publications, a resolution as follows:
{{quote|Savenko Yu. S. in his public appearances has grossly violated the norms of professional ethics. In numerous declarations, appeals, appearances by Savenko Yu. S. in the media, there are noted impermissible, insulting, offensive statements, which derogate from honour, dignity and goodwill of both individual experts and the expert institution F[ederal] S[tate] B[udgetary] I[nstitution] "the Serbsky S[tate] S[cientific] C[enter for] S[ocial and] F[orensic] P[sychiatry]" and at the same time undermine the authority of the psychiatric community as a whole.<ref>{{cite web|title=Постановление Комиссии правления Российского общества психиатров по вопросам профессиональной этики|trans-title=The resolution by the Commission on Professional Ethics Issues at the Board of the Russian Society of Psychiatrists|url=http://psychiatr.ru/news/197|publisher=The Russian Society of Psychiatrists|accessdate=16 January 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116075111/http:/psychiatr.ru/download/1398?view=1&name=1396.pdf|archivedate=16 January 2014}}</ref>}}
Savenko responded that the strikingly unethical nature of the resolution by the Ethical Commission (of 12 December 2013) showed in the ascription to the IPA open letter to the WPA, hosted on the website, of phrases that were never used there.<ref name=Outcomes>{{cite web|author=Savenko, Yuri [Юрий Савенко]|script-title=ru:Президент НПА России Ю.С.Савенко анализирует итоги дела Михаила Косенко|trans-title=The President of the IPA of Russia Yu.S. Savenko analyzes the outcomes of the case of Mikhail Kosenko|url=http://npar.ru/prezident-npa-rossii-yu-s-savenko-analiziruet-itogi-dela-mixaila-kosenko/|publisher=[[Independent Psychiatric Association of Russia]]|accessdate=3 February 2014|date=1 February 2014|language=Russian}}</ref> He adds we see a rather awkward performance of a social role using the old scenario of accusatory campaigns of Soviet times to have the possibility to refer to "the opinion of the professional public" for use abroad.<ref name=Outcomes/>
== Awards == On 10 December 2013, Savenko received the award of the [[Moscow Helsinki Group]] "for historic contribution to the defence of human rights and the human rights movement".<ref>{{cite news|title=Лия Ахеджакова стала лауреатом премии Московской Хельсинкской группы|url=http://www.rg.ru/2013/12/10/ahedjakova-anons.html|accessdate=24 December 2013|newspaper=[[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]]|date=10 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Лия Ахеджакова удостоена премии за защиту прав человека|url=http://top.rbc.ru/society/10/12/2013/893881.shtml|accessdate=24 December 2013|date=10 December 2013}}</ref>
